                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the west and south bases of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> inside the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kṛishṇadēvarāya. Ś. 1437: 1515 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date given, viz., Śaka 1437, Bhāva, Āḍi 9, correspond to 1515 A.D. July 8. The Śaka year quoted was current.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records the grant of 2 pieces of land to a Śaiva-maṭha presided over by Tiruvakkarai Tirukkāḷatti Pichchan Meññāṉa(<hi rend="italic">Meyjñāṉa</hi>)-māmuṉi for <hi rend="italic">māhēśvarapūjā</hi>, by Tirumalai Nāyaka,<note>Compare <hi rend="italic">A.R. Ep.</hi>, 1924, No. 145.</note> and the <hi rend="italic">śrībhaṇḍārattār</hi> of the temple.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
